  "body": "*Title*: *Allow setting a list of constant tags for Tracing*\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\n>Currently there is an option for adding tags based on http request headers (request_headers_for_tags). However, there is no option for passing a list of hardcoded tags. It would be great to have such a feature. For example variables like node_id, host_ip, or pod_name could be added to the traces as follows, enriching the traces at will.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"tracing\": {\r\n  \"operation_name\": \"egress\",\r\n  \"request_headers_for_tags\": [\r\n    \"x-cdp-sdk\",\r\n    \"x-cdp-app\",\r\n    \"x-cdp-clienttag\"\r\n   ],\r\n   \"constant_tags\": [\r\n     \"node_ip=x.x.x.x\",\r\n      \"pod_name=pod-xyz\"\r\n    ]\r\n },\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt should be an easy task for someone that knows the codebase. Thank you in advance.\r\n\r\n",
